FBIS4-13104 "drnes074_n_94010" FBIS-NES-94-074 Daily Report 17 Apr 1994 LEBANON Israeli Mock Raids, Shelling Reported Israeli Mock Raids, Shelling Reported NC1704161694 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1530 GMT 17 Apr 94 NC1704161694 Beirut Radio Lebanon Arabic BFN [Text] Israeli warplanes staged several sorties over the south this morning, specifically over the al-Nabatiyah and the Iqlim al-Tuffah areas. They staged two mock raids at low altitude and broke the sound barrier. The eastern hills and the outskirts of Kafr Rumman came under heavy machine-gun fire at 0800 today from the Israeli forces' positions in al-Dabshah. In the central sector, the outskirts of the town of Yatar came under intensive machine-gun fire at midnight last night while the sky overhead was lit by flares. In the Marj 'Uyun area, an agent Lahd [South Lebanese Army] unit combed with machine-gun fire the main road that links Marj 'Uyun with the Zumarayya crossing point and that passes through the al-Khiyan junction and the Nab' al-Hasbani. According to information received from the occupied strip, the SLA command interrogated a number of its members following the explosion of a device under one of its patrols at the entrance to Marj 'Uyun three days ago. The explosion killed recruit Faris Ilyas Jabbur from Kawkaba and injured another.
